180. For Saturnus see Vocabulary of Proper Names. According to legend he came to Italy after being dethroned by Juppiter, and his reign was a Golden Age. Janus was the oldest Italian national god. His name is the same as Dianus, masculine of Diana, a sun-god, god of the morning, god of all beginning, and god of gates. He was two-faced to look in and out of the gate.
